28. Tanaum: this is the manuscript reading, for which most editions read Taum, Tay. But Agricola did not reach the Tay, as is shown by the next chapter. It was probably the Tyne, just north of Dunbar, the only estuary of any size on the Scottish coast south of the Forth.
